track_length=int(len(bounce) * 10)
#created a duel channel of 10 times the lenght of single bounse
sig = np.array([np.zeros(track_length), np.zeros(track_length)])

#Length of each chop is varible decreses as we go 
chop = 1/10
chop_size = int(len(bounce))
n = 10
i=0
my_len=0
while True:
    if i==0:
        chop_at = 0
    
    #decresing the gap between the adjecent bounces    
    if(i!=0):
        chop_size-= int(chop_size/(i*100))
    
    #save lenght of trak appened till now    
    my_len+=chop_size
   
    # if lenght of append track exceed the track lenght 
    if(my_len>track_length):
        break
    #Get a section from where the next bounnce starts
    new_bounse = bounce[chop_at:chop_at+chop_size]*(n-i)

#     Speed up the bounce as ball comes closer to the ground
    if i>0:
        #pitch increase with the increase in the i *2
        new_bounse= librosa.resample(new_bounse, sr, int(sr/((2)*i)))
        
# Slowing down of the bounse impact    
        new_bounse = (new_bounse*2)/i

        
        
    #Pick channel based on if i is even or odd
    chan = i%2
    #Overwrite with new bounce
    start = i*chop_size
    end = start + len(new_bounse)
    sig[chan,start:end] = new_bounse
    i+=1
    
show_audio(sig, sr)
